Document_summary: This document is an application by Hawaiian Electric Company seeking approval for a Power Purchase Agreement with Waiawa PV, LLC for a solar project in Hawaii. The document outlines the project details, requested approvals, and financial impacts. The application emphasizes the importance of timely approval to meet project milestones and regulatory requirements.

This document is a revised Community-Based Renewable Energy Program Phase 1, outlining the availability, customer participation, credit rates, O&M fees, developer participation, and requirements for the CBRE Program. It sets eligibility criteria for residential and commercial customers, details the process for participants to purchase energy output interests, and specifies upfront payments, O&M fees, and credit rates for participants and developers.
Suggested_title_v3: 11-30-2015 Community-Based Renewable Energy Program Phase 1 Summary.pdf

Document_summary: This document is an application for approval of a Power Purchase Agreement (PPA) for Renewable Dispatchable Generation with Waiawa Phase 2 Solar, LLC. The PPA aims to provide Hawaiian Electric dispatch rights over renewable energy facilities, enabling the company to meet energy and grid service requirements. The document outlines the benefits of the PPA, including bill savings for customers, reduced fossil fuel consumption, and increased renewable energy contributions to meet state goals.

This document is a Letter of Intent between Haleakala Ranch Company and Clearway Renew LLC for the development of a 40 megawatt solar renewable energy project in Maui County, Hawaii. The implications are that the parties are agreeing to negotiate the terms of definitive agreements for the project.

This document is an Interconnection Agreement between Kauai Island Utility Cooperative and Kapaa Solar LLC, outlining the terms and conditions for the interconnection of a Small Generating Facility. It covers responsibilities, costs, termination, disputes, insurance, confidentiality, and other miscellaneous provisions. The Agreement emphasizes compliance with Applicable Laws and Regulations, Good Distributed Generation Practice, and infrastructure security measures.

This document provides detailed information on two solar projects in different stages of development, including capacity, cost per watt, next steps, and off-taker status. It outlines key aspects such as permitting, interconnection, and potential off-taker agreements.

The document is an application for approval of a Power Purchase Agreement between Hawaiian Electric Company, Inc. and Kalaeloa Solar Two, LLC. It outlines the terms and conditions of the agreement, including the construction and interconnection of the solar facility, pricing structure, and implications for meeting Hawaii's Renewable Energy Portfolio Standards.

This document is a Purchase and Sale Agreement between Waikoloa Highlands, Inc. and Waikoloa Land Holdings, LLC for a property in Waikoloa, Hawaii. The agreement outlines the sale of approximately 706.63 acres of land for the development of a Solar Project, contingent on various milestones including HELCO's selection process. The document is in the stage of finalizing terms and conditions for the property sale.
